Dangote Cement, a company owned by Aliko Dangote, African s richest man with interests all over the world, has revealed that it has approached South Africa s cement giant, PPC for a takeover deal.A report from Bloomberg, quoting a statement from Dangote Cement, to the Nigerian Stock Exchange, has disclosed that Dangote Cement has communicated its interest to PPC s board with respect to the entire of the entire share capital . Dangote s approach follows a joint offer from Canada s Fairfax Financial and domestic rival AfriSam. However, analysts believe that the Public Investment Corporation (PIC), the largest shareholder, is likely to consider Afrisam s offer.